==English==

===Etymology===
Derived from the working of this form of iron; [[wrought]] is the old past and past participle of to [[work]], a wrought metal is one that is hammered into shape. See [[cast iron]] for comparison

===Noun===
'''[[wrought]] [[iron]]'''

# A tough, malleable, ductile form of iron that is not cast, suitable for welding.

